  "verdicts": [
   {
    "assertion_id": "a1",
    "verdict": "unverifiable",
    "evidence": "Telemetry shows steering input was small pre-impact then a large change at impact; steering baseline median [7.5 deg](T4) with a peak [40.5 deg at t=0.0](T2). However, there is no sensor channel that records lateral position or shoulder departure, so whether the vehicle \"drifted onto the shoulder\" cannot be determined from these channels alone and is unverifiable."
   },
   {
    "assertion_id": "a2",
    "verdict": "contradicted",
    "evidence": "The crash pulse shows a large negative longitudinal delta-V reaching [\u221298.6 km/h at t=0.24 s](T4) and the cumulative delta-V series begins negative immediately after impact (e.g. [\u22122.9 km/h at 0.01 s](T3)), indicating a strong deceleration (vehicle struck something ahead or experienced a severe frontal-like impulse). That pattern contradicts an assertion that the contact was a light bump with the parked trailer's rear (which would produce little longitudinal delta-V). The sensors therefore contradict the claimed low-severity rear impact orientation."
   },
   {
    "assertion_id": "a3",
    "verdict": "contradicted",
    "evidence": "The delta-V time series shows a single, large crash pulse accumulating to about [\u221298.2 km/h final delta-V at 0.25 s](T3) with no separate, multiple distinct small impact spikes; the EDR summary reports a max longitudinal delta-V of [\u221299.1 km/h](T1). This magnitude is far larger than a single light bump, so the characterization of \"a single bump\" as minor is contradicted by the recorded severe single impact magnitude."
   },
   {
    "assertion_id": "a4",
    "verdict": "contradicted",
    "evidence": "The EDR summary reports a maximum longitudinal delta-V of [\u221299.1 km/h](T1) and the crash pulse reaches about [\u221298.6 km/h at t=0.24 s](T3), which are values consistent with a high-severity impact, contradicting the claim that the collision was a light tap."
   },
   {
    "assertion_id": "a5",
    "verdict": "unverifiable",
    "evidence": "There is no telemetry channel indicating the other object's motion; delta-V shows the subject vehicle experienced a large deceleration ([final \u221298.2 km/h](T3)), but that alone does not prove whether the trailer was stationary or moving, so the parked trailer being stationary is unverifiable from these sensors."
   },
   {
    "assertion_id": "a6",
    "verdict": "unverifiable",
    "evidence": "There are pre-crash speed and RPM values (speed around [96 km/h just before impact](T2) and brake release at [\u22122.75 s transition](T4)), but post-impact driveability (vehicle could be driven away) cannot be determined from the provided telemetry; damage or subsequent engine/transmission function is not recorded, so this is unverifiable."
   },
   {
    "assertion_id": "a7",
    "verdict": "unverifiable",
    "evidence": "The sequence claim depends on lateral roadway position; while steering shows a peak at impact ([40.5 deg at t=0.0](T2)) and brakes were released at [\u22122.75 s](T4), there is no lateral-position or shoulder-detection channel to establish that drifting onto the shoulder occurred before impact, so the temporal sequence is unverifiable."
   }
  ],
